Class UserPlane

All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class UserPlane extends FighterPlane
Represents the user's plane in the game. The user plane can move in all directions, fire projectiles, and can use a multi-shot feature to fire multiple projectiles at once. It tracks kills and includes various functionalities such as controlling the plane's movement and handling the firing mechanics.

    • fireMultiShot

      public List<GameObject> fireMultiShot()
      Fires multiple projectiles at once (triple-shot) if the multi-shot power-up is enabled and the cooldown period has passed. If the power-up is not enabled, a single projectile is fired. Returns an empty list if the plane is disabled or the cooldown period is active.
      Returns:
      A list of projectiles fired or an empty list if conditions are not met.

    • enableMultiShot

      public void enableMultiShot()
      Enables the multi-shot power-up for the user's plane for a duration of 10 seconds. During this time, the plane will fire three projectiles at once.

    • isMultishotEnabled

      public boolean isMultishotEnabled()
      Returns the current status of the multi-shot power-up.
      Returns:
      true if multi-shot is enabled, false otherwise.
